After a year, this holdout reports a confidence sequence of
\[0\.18%\, 1\.82%\] and an ordinary interval of \[0\.47%\, 1\.53%\]. The
confidence sequence is wider because it provides simultaneous coverage across
all 52 reviews; the ordinary interval provides pointwise coverage at a single
review. This scenario has no stopping rule. The sequence itself is reported at
each review.

For each of the 100 simulated holdouts, the next
calculation checks whether the reported interval contained the true lift at
every review so far:

::: {#19ecc947 .cell execution_count=17}
